{
  "texts": [
    "Existing DDI prediction methods based on GNNs typically leverage the topological and semantic modeling capabilities of GNNs to represent drugs.",
    "Then, they learn the representations of drug pairs by considering the respective representations of each drug involved [15].",
    "MR-GNN [16] uses an end-to-end GNN to obtain graph-structured entity structural features.",
    "Molormer [17] uses the two-dimensional structural information of a drug as input and encodes the molecular graph with spatial information for DDI task prediction.",
    "A drug can also be divided into several functional groups or chemical substructures, leading to certain pharmacological properties [18]."
  ]
}